rm(list = ls()) 
link='https://github.com/Bearnamedjoey/guided1/raw/main/Updated_Country_Comparison.csv'
myFile=url(link)
fromPy=read.csv(file = myFile)
row.names(fromPy)=NULL
str(fromPy)
'data.frame':   85 obs. of  7 variables:
 $ Country               : chr  "Argentina" "Bolivia" "Colombia" "Paraguay" ...
 $ Years                 : num  32.4 25.3 31.2 29.7 31.1 47.8 38.4 40.6 28.8 37.5 ...

 $ Gini.Index            : num  42.3 43.6 54.2 46.2 37.9 31.7 38.2 34.8 47.3 34.3 ...
 $ Airports              : num  916 855 836 799 673 539 507 460 432 418 ...
dataToCluster=fromPy[,-c(1)]
row.names(dataToCluster)=fromPy$Country
set.seed(999)
library(cluster)
distanceMatrix=daisy(x=dataToCluster, metric = "gower")
projectedData = cmdscale(distanceMatrix, k=2)
fromPy$dim1 = projectedData[,1]
fromPy$dim2 = projectedData[,2]
library(ggplot2)
base= ggplot(data=fromPy,
             aes(x=dim1, y=dim2,
                 label=Country)) 
base + geom_text(size=2)

hc = hclust(distanceMatrix)
plot(hc,hang = -1,cex=0.5)

NumberOfClusterDesired=4

library(factoextra)
fviz_nbclust(dataToCluster, 
             hcut,
             diss=distanceMatrix,
             method = "gap_stat",
             k.max = 10,
             verbose = F,
             hc_func = "agnes")
